			<h1>Learning to Use the Abacus</h1>
			<h2>Why Learn Math on the Abacus?</h2>
			<p>The abacus is a tool that facilitates the mind in making calculations beyond what is typically possible. Although abacus users have the capability to do complex mathematics, it is the discipline itself that trains students to expect more from themselves. A well trained abacus master does not need a physical abacus, rather they visualize one and manipulate the beads mentally. This level of skill is achieved through years of daily training; however, it is never too early to start working on visualization skills. It is popular to send young children to study the abacus in an attempt to increase their visual memory, expose them to new challenges and give them a head start in math. Learning to use an abacus instills good study practices that students can carry with them through their life. </p>
