			<h2>Where to Begin Learning Abacus?</h2>
			<p>While it is possible to self-teach abacus, most students join one of the many abacus clubs in their area. Either way, it is a years-long commitment that requires daily practice to progress to new skills. Students can get started with the <%= link_to 'Abacus Fundamentals Course', '/dir/beginner.html', :relative => true %> so they can sum any three-digit numbers on the abacus in preparation for more advanced math. This is great supplemental material for those who join an abacus club to get some extra practice.</p>


			<p>Every abacus school is unique so it is ideal to meet with instructors from different clubs to discus expectations. One key point to investigate is their approach to teaching visualization skills and at what level it is introduced. Some teach students to visualize the abacus from the very beginning and other schools leave it for more advanced users. There is also a lot of variation in finger movement techniques from school-to-school with some schools using only two fingers and others using two hands. Classes can be costly but do provide an established stepwise process to move through.</p> 
 
